docs.abstract: Jake Siewert led the firm’s post-financial crisis reputation makeover.
docs.snippet: Jake Siewert led the firm’s post-financial crisis reputation makeover.
docs.lead_paragraph: For nearly a decade, Jake Siewert led Goldman Sachs’s post-crisis efforts to shed its image as one of Wall Street’s most mysterious, and maligned, money machines. We’re the first to report that he plans to announce his departure later today.

headline.main: Goldman Sachs’s Top Image Maker Is Leaving

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Jason Karaian, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni
